fields.name: single-link-node
fields.description: This is a node that contains one reference point to another node in memory

fields.name: list-head
fields.description: The first element in a linked list

fields.name: list-size
fields.description: List size is an integer value that initializes at 0 and is iterated upwards by 1 for every new value carrying node that is added to the list and iterated downward by 1 for every value carrying node that is removed from the list.

fields.name: list-push
fields.description: Add element to end of list

fields.name: list-peek
fields.description: See the value of the head element of a list without removing it from the list

fields.name: list-is-empty
fields.description: Determines whether linked list has any value bearing elements and returns a boolean
